Hermes Eau Des Merveilles Eau de Toilette - 100 ml (For Women) Price: Rs.8500

As she trails her feet on the water’s edge Hermes Eau de Merveilles scintillates like the lights that twinkle in the distance. She gently captures the errant firefly that flits too close to her and watches in wonder as its little light illuminates the dark night just like the exquisite perfume lights up her own life. Since its launch in 2004 this luxury fragrance has been a favorite with discerning audiences for the magical aura that it exudes.

This sparkling Eau de Toilette was created by perfumers Ralf Schwieger and Nathalie Feisthauer. The fragrance has happy opening notes of orange and lemon which lend a crisp citrusy air to it. Amber and pink pepper rule the heart along with faint accords of violet and pepper. The spiciness fades onto a base of Madagascar vetiver oakmoss and fir. Cedar brings up the rear leaving a trail of beautiful woodiness in the dry down. Bottled in a oval transparent bottle with splashes of orange on the base the beautiful flacon accentuates the sparkle of the fragrance and gives the infusion an aura of enchantment. Be wrapped in cloak of magic and float on the cloud of intimate delicacy that is Hermes Eau Des Merveilles.

column17:
Hermes Terre D' Hermes Eau de Toilette - 100 ml (For Women) Price: Rs.9999

She digs her feet into the warm sand and lifts her face up to raindrops; she is a woman of the earth through and through. Hermes presents an ode to her in the luxurious warmth of Terre D’Hermes which is a metaphor for a matrix that speaks of matter earth and roots. The Eau de Parfum envelops her in a cozy blanket of fragrance as she runs her hand across the iron rungs of the window taking in the deeply touching smell of the freshly wetted earth.

Created in 2006 by perfumer Jean-Claude Ellena Terre D’Hermes is a mildly surprising infusion of the choicest of elements. The opening notes of citrusy orange and bitter grapefruit add vivacity to the fragrance. The heart hides spicy pepper and pelargonium which rest on a base of patchouli cedar and vetiver. Benzoin imparts a depth that lasts long after the dry down fades and flirts with the senses for a long time to come.

The flacon holding the amber fragrance has a characteristic resemblance of the Greek god Hermes’ wings. This vertically structured scent embraces the uninhibited nature of femininity enhancing it to heights of irresistibleness.
